{"TopicId":203768,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"What do you NOT want in KSP 2","CreatedByName":"MKI","CreatedById":77241,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-12T21:19:07Z","PageNum":6,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Hyperspace Industries","CreatedById":212417,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-10T05:02:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA bad sandbox, or even worse, no sandbox mode, I love playing sandbox, it\u2019s more fun for me.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ash73","CreatedById":15228,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T02:14:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMultiplayer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will ruin the game, and diverts effort away from useful new features.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is simply no way to do it sensibly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mcwaffles2003","CreatedById":180102,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T08:45:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224010232\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627350947\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/26/2021 at 9:55 PM, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFree reusability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecovering a space craft should cost money, not refund it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t this already exist? The farther from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E you recover from the less of the rockets value you have returned. (transportation costs)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224035960\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632536099\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002215228\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ash73\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, ash73 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMultiplayer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will ruin the game, and diverts effort away from useful new features.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is simply no way to do it sensibly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you figure?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Staticalliam7","CreatedById":216180,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T15:22:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe kraken maybe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe none of the dumb\u00A0 bugs we have in ksp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwho am i kidding\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-25T15:23:36Z\u0022 title=\u002209/25/2021 03:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 25, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Staticalliam7\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T17:16:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224035960\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632536099\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002215228\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ash73\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, ash73 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMultiplayer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will ruin the game, and diverts effort away from useful new features.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is simply no way to do it sensibly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is simply false and it\u0027s not even a matter of opinion, KSP as a game whether you want to see it from the simulator side or the management game side is the perfect kind of game for Coop Multiplayer, there are multiple ways to do it sensibly if you\u0027re not expecting a MMO kind of experience, for 2-8 players to completely play a career together you just need a simple sync-desync system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Synonym Toast Crunch","CreatedById":216191,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T20:22:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMetallic hydrogen of course, but I\u0027ll make due with just not researching that tech tree branch. Hopefully it has\u00A0its own tech tree branch\u00A0that doesn\u0027t have other stuff locked behind it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T20:41:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224019891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628955789\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212713\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSP_linux0191\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/14/2021 at 4:43 PM, KSP_linux0191 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t want a flat UI, e.g. flat buttons. KSP\u0027s UI looks cool because\u00A0the buttons have shaders that make them look round. Adding shaders to make things look 3D on 2D improves the look of anything it\u0027s applied to, period.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it made the UI cluttered, piling onto the fact that the UI is all over the place. KSP 2\u0027s UI needs less time to be processed and there\u0027s less visual clutter preventing that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632590200\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002268648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Master39\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Master39 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor 2-8 players to completely play a career together you just need a simple sync-desync system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgree. Multiplayer mods previously have fixed the problem of timewarp in a way that grants everyone control and lets people meet willingly and easily, then many years later there ends up being so much buzz over how multiplayer timewarp could be done, like everyone in the world just forgot Dark Multiplayer was ever a thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T20:57:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224024010\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629878605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201818\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Clamp-o-Tron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/25/2021 at 9:03 AM, Clamp-o-Tron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s not a normal occurrence for 95% of players.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds about right... with most other games, that figure would be 99.8%.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-27T19:39:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJet engine smoke. Unless above 7.5 clicks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSP_linux0191","CreatedById":212713,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T01:36:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632602489\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/25/2021 at 4:41 PM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it made the UI cluttered, piling onto the fact that the UI is all over the place. KSP 2\u0027s UI needs less time to be processed and there\u0027s less visual clutter preventing that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point is against a flat UI, not a cluttered UI. And you can de-clutter it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T12:58:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224038609\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633138593\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212713\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSP_linux0191\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, KSP_linux0191 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point is against a flat UI, not a cluttered UI. And you can de-clutter it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I\u0027m saying that your idea would make the UI feel cluttered. The team is taking the UI in the right direction by making it flat, helping reduce clutter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSP_linux0191","CreatedById":212713,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T19:05:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am not speaking of cluttered arrangements. I am speaking of using shaders to make e.g. a button look like it is rounded, sticking out of the surface it is embedded in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022stylish-3d-buttons-photoshop-psds.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.00\u0022 height=\u0022490\u0022 width=\u0022700\u0022 src=\u0022https://static.brusheezy.com/system/resources/previews/000/003/335/non_2x/stylish-3d-buttons-photoshop-psds.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin contrast to this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ok-button-37865.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022256\u0022 width=\u0022256\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.iconscout.com/icon/free/png-256/ok-button-37865.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jastrone","CreatedById":208489,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T20:07:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224035960\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632536099\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002215228\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ash73\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/25/2021 at 4:14 AM, ash73 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMultiplayer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will ruin the game, and diverts effort away from useful new features.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is simply no way to do it sensibly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow will it ruin the game? even if we would get a few less features it would defenetly be worth it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T20:25:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224038922\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633201543\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212713\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSP_linux0191\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, KSP_linux0191 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am not speaking of cluttered arrangements. I am speaking of using shaders to make e.g. a button look like it is rounded, sticking out of the surface it is embedded in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich would make it feel cluttered. Do you get what I\u0027m saying now? The flat texturing makes the UI look a lot more readable, and doesn\u0027t take as much time to process what I\u0027m looking at.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSP_linux0191","CreatedById":212713,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-03T19:38:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224038954\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633206356\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich would make it feel cluttered. Do you get what I\u0027m saying now? The flat texturing makes the UI look a lot more readable, and doesn\u0027t take as much time to process what I\u0027m looking at.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI get what you are saying now. Maybe there should be an option to install/make themes; some that have 3D buttons and stuff, and some that are flat. That would satisfy both sides.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}